## Animation System

### Timing Functions

```css
/* Natural ease (recommended for most animations) */
transition-timing-function: cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94)

/* Mechanical (precise, UI elements) */
transition-timing-function: cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1)

/* Entrance (elements appearing) */
transition-timing-function: cubic-bezier(0, 0, 0.2, 1)

/* Exit (elements leaving) */
transition-timing-function: cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 1, 1)
```

### Duration Standards

```css
fast:   200ms  /* Micro-interactions, hover states */
base:   300ms  /* Default transitions */
slow:   600ms  /* Page transitions, important UI changes */
slower: 1000ms /* Hero animations, special effects */
```

### Animation Patterns

**Fade In**
```tsx
<motion.div
  initial={{ opacity: 0 }}
  animate={{ opacity: 1 }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.6, ease: naturalEase }}
/>
```

**Slide Up**
```tsx
<motion.div
  initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 40 }}
  animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.6, ease: naturalEase }}
/>
```

**Scale In**
```tsx
<motion.div
  initial={{ opacity: 0, scale: 0.95 }}
  animate={{ opacity: 1, scale: 1 }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.6, ease: naturalEase }}
/>
```

